    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1737978353" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1737978353" />
    <a title="Suzy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6942006-suzy"><img alt="Suzy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1565275031p2/6942006.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1737978353?book_show_action=true">Sep 11, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Suzy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Suzy" href="/user/show/6942006-suzy">Suzy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780553418774" href="/book/show/23278537-the-little-paris-bookshop">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6942006-suzy?shelf=journeying">journeying</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6942006-suzy?shelf=found-family">found-family</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6942006-suzy?shelf=found-community">found-community</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6942006-suzy?shelf=books-n-bookshops">books-n-bookshops</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1737978353" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7954185580296023035">This story of a Parisian bookseller who sets out on his bookstore on a barge to find the lover who abandoned him 20 years ago started out on a promising note but very quickly devolved. So many times I was rolling my eyes and groaning . . . and not in a good way. :) I felt the author was trying way too hard to be poignant and profound - maybe wanting to be the next Elizabeth Gilbert?<br/><br/>So why did I read to the end of this almost 400 page book and rate it 3 stars instead of 1 or 2? There were several</span>
  <span id="freeText7954185580296023035" style="display:none">This story of a Parisian bookseller who sets out on his bookstore on a barge to find the lover who abandoned him 20 years ago started out on a promising note but very quickly devolved. So many times I was rolling my eyes and groaning . . . and not in a good way. :) I felt the author was trying way too hard to be poignant and profound - maybe wanting to be the next Elizabeth Gilbert?<br /><br />So why did I read to the end of this almost 400 page book and rate it 3 stars instead of 1 or 2? There were several things I did enjoy, primarily the descriptions of place. The book starts in Paris and our bookseller, Jean Perdu, travels partially by boat and then by car to Sanary-sur-Mer on the Mediterranean. I felt like I was taking the journey with them, experiencing the country through their eyes. I also loved the idea that Perdu's bookstore on a boat was billed as a Literary Apothecary, where instead of just selling books, he would prescribe books based on what customers needed. He was writing an encyclopedia of "small emotions" as a guide to selecting books for specific things people were feeling. Clever! Lastly, I came to like many of the characters and they are (amazingly) sticking with me.<br /><br />But there were not enough of those good things for me to endorse this book. And what about the title? I didn't get the feeling that this bookshop was little and 2/3 of the book does not take place in Paris - since the bookstore was on a boat, he took it with him. </span>
  <a data-text-id="7954185580296023035" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


